history.content:
EECS126, CS189 and a light tech should be doable. Have no idea of Physics but if it is a hard technical class, you'd better not take it with 126 and 189.

From workload perspective EECS126 and CS170 has similar workload. Which to choose really depends on whether you want to be software oriented (take 170 early) or theory oriented (take 126 to better understand ML)

Hi, I'm currently a sophomore and am definitely planning to take CS189 and Data 8 next semester. But for other courses, I am unsure of whether to take CS170 or CS126. I might also take an upper div physics course like 110A (I might try for a physics minor). What would be more helpful to have earlier, CS170 or CS126? Also, how manageable would CS189, CS126, Data 8, and physics 110A be? Or would it be recommeneded to just replace physics 110A with an ethics course?

I haven't taken any upper div courses yet so I'm not sure how they compare to the lower div courses I have taken so far. Any advice on the differences between upper and lower div courses regarding workload or anything else? Thanks.
history.subject: Advice on Workload: CS126, CS189, and upper div physics
